Preheat the #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @Baby Potatoes{500%grams} lengthways, quartering any larger pieces. Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} then season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Rub the oil over the potatoes then lay them cut-side down on the baking tray.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until fork tender, ~{25-35%minutes}.

Trim the @Cucumber{2} then halve lengthways.

Bash each half with the bottom of a #pot or #pan. Thinly slice widthways.

In a separate #bowl, toss the smashed cucumber with @Sugar{1%tsp} half the @Soy Sauce{2%sachet} and the @Apple Cider Vinegar{1%sachet}.

Set aside, continuing to stir occasionally.

Place a pan over medium heat (no oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @Sesame Seeds{1%sachet} until lightly toasted, stirring regularly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the pan and set aside.

In a #small bowl{}, make the glaze by mixing @Miso Paste{1%sachet}, @Honey{2%sachet} and the remaining soy sauce.

Toss the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%grams} with salt, pepper and @Flour{2%tbsp}.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Fry the chicken until browned and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

Pour in the miso glaze and @Garlic, Ginger & Lemongrass Paste{1%sachet}.

Cook until thickened, ~{2%minutes}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from the chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, place the @Bao Buns{1%pack} on a #plate (3 at a time). Microwave covered for ~{1%minute}.

Keep covered until serving.

> TIP: Don't have a microwave? Place a large pot with 2cm of water over high heat. Once boiling, place a #colander lined with a #baking sheet{} on the pot. Place the bao (3 at a time) on the baking sheet, cover and steam for 3-4 mins.

Fill each bao bun with a little smashed cucumber and some miso chicken.

Plate up your baos with the roasted potatoes alongside.

Sprinkle the toasted sesame seeds over everything.

Scatter the bao buns with @Dried Chilli Flakes{2%sachet}.

Serve any remaining smashed cucumber salad on the side.